#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:4
msgid "Using profiles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:6
msgid ""
"So far, we have used the default settings stored in ``~/.conan/profiles/"
"default`` and defined custom values for some of them as command line "
"arguments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:8
msgid ""
"However, in large projects, configurations can get complex, settings can be "
"very different, and we need an easy way to switch between different "
"configurations with different settings, options etc. An easy way to switch "
"between configurations is by using profiles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:11
msgid ""
"A profile file contains a predefined set of ``settings``, ``options``, "
"``environment variables``, and ``build_requires`` specified in the following "
"structure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:13
msgid ""
"[settings]\n"
"setting=value\n"
"\n"
"[options]\n"
"MyLib:shared=True\n"
"\n"
"[env]\n"
"env_var=value\n"
"\n"
"[build_requires]\n"
"tool1/0.1@user/channel\n"
"tool2/0.1@user/channel, tool3/0.1@user/channel\n"
"*: tool4/0.1@user/channel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:29
msgid ""
"Options allow the use of wildcards letting you apply the same option value "
"to many packages. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:31
msgid ""
"[options]\n"
"*:shared=True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:36
msgid "Here is an example of a configuration that a profile file may contain:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:38
msgid "*clang_3.5*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:38
msgid ""
" [settings]\n"
" os=Macos\n"
" arch=x86_64\n"
" compiler=clang\n"
" compiler.version=3.5\n"
" compiler.libcxx=libstdc++11\n"
" build_type=Release\n"
"\n"
" [env]\n"
" CC=/usr/bin/clang-3.5\n"
" CXX=/usr/bin/clang++-3.5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:53
msgid ""
"A profile file can be stored in the default profile folder, or anywhere else "
"in your project file structure. To use the configuration specified in a "
"profile file, pass in the file as a command line argument as shown in the "
"example below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:55
msgid "$ conan create . demo/testing -pr=clang_3.5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:59
msgid ""
"Continuing with the example of Poco, instead of passing in a long list of "
"command line arguments, we can define a handy profile that defines them all "
"and pass that to the command line when installing the project dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:61
msgid ""
"A profile to install dependencies as **shared** and in **debug** mode would "
"look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:63
msgid "*debug_shared*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:63
msgid ""
" include(default)\n"
"\n"
" [settings]\n"
" build_type=Debug\n"
"\n"
" [options]\n"
" poco:shared=True\n"
" poco:enable_apacheconnector=False\n"
" openssl:shared=True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:76
msgid "To install dependencies using the profile file, we would use:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:78
msgid "$ conan install .. -pr=debug_shared"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:82
msgid ""
"We could also create a new profile to use a different compiler version and "
"store that in our project directory. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:84
msgid "*poco_clang_3.5*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:84
msgid ""
" include(clang_3.5)\n"
"\n"
" [options]\n"
" poco:shared=True\n"
" poco:enable_apacheconnector=False\n"
" openssl:shared=True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:94
msgid "To install dependencies using this new profile, we would use:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:96
msgid "$ conan install .. -pr=../poco_clang_3.5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:100
msgid ""
"You can specify multiple profiles in the command line. The applied "
"configuration will be the composition of all the profiles applied in the "
"order they are specified:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:103
msgid ""
"$ conan install .. -pr=../poco_clang_3.5 -pr=my_build_tool1 -"
"pr=my_build_tool2"
msgstr ""

